  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Signing Safe Futures</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Deaf children and young people are particularly vulnerable to abuse and exploitation. They can be seen as easy prey by abusers because they are unable to communicate or report what is happening to them. Anecdotal evidence of such difficulties experienced by deaf children has emerged in South Africa and other countries. This research will look at the situation in South Africa to understand the prevalence and nature of the abuse suffered by deaf children there. The results of the study will be used to design a nationwide programme to address these problems. The outcome will be that deaf children are better protected from exploitation and abuse.</narrative>
  </description>
